{"TopicId":220558,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Native widescreen support","CreatedByName":"DwightLee","CreatedById":199897,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-01T13:22:52Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"DwightLee","CreatedById":199897,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-01T13:22:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow that KSP 2 is becoming playable, we really need native support for ultra-wide monitors, 5120x1440 please\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LoSBoL","CreatedById":174038,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-01T14:11:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI second this request\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"whatsEJstandfor","CreatedById":220814,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-01T16:11:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224335858\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221698844972\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199897\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DwightLee\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, DwightLee said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow that KSP 2 is becoming playable, we really need native support for ultra-wide monitors, 5120x1440 please\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe nice thing is that it already (mostly) works out of the box by editing settings.json. Legit the only issue I\u0027ve noticed is that the loading screen images are stretched out, but I can\u0027t think of anything else that\u0027s been broken at that resolution.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LoSBoL","CreatedById":174038,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-01T16:29:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224335915\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221698855089\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022220814\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022whatsEJstandfor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 minutes ago, whatsEJstandfor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe nice thing is that it already (mostly) works out of the box by editing settings.json. Legit the only issue I\u0027ve noticed is that the loading screen images are stretched out, but I can\u0027t think of anything else that\u0027s been broken at that resolution.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBroken might be a bit overstretched, but with the latest update I am getting KSP1 UI vibes because of the bottom UI elements have now been stretches across the whole bottom instead of grouped mostly to the left.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/220393-please-revert-to-grouped-ui-elements-again-instead-of-spreading-them/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttps://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/220393-please-revert-to-grouped-ui-elements-again-instead-of-spreading-them/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-01T22:28:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThread moved to suggestions.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DwightLee","CreatedById":199897,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-02T09:39:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\